Using the fact that 9 = 3^2, we write each side of the equation as a power of 3:
\begin{align*}
3^{x-2} \amp = 9^3 \\
3^{x-2} \amp = \left(3^2\right)^3 \\
3^{x-2} \amp = 3^6.
\end{align*}
Now we equate the exponents to obtain
\begin{align*}
x - 2 \amp = 6 \\
x  \amp = 8.
\end{align*}

We write each factor as a power of 3.

	\begin{aligned}
	27 \cdot 3^{-2x} \amp= 9^{x+1} \\
	3^3 \cdot 3^{-2x} \amp= \left(3^2\right)^{x+1}
	\end{aligned}

We use the laws of exponents to simplify each side:
3^{3-2x} = 3^{2x+2}.
Now we equate the exponents to obtain
\begin{align*}
3 - 2x \amp = 2x + 2 \\
-4x =\amp  -1.
\end{align*}
The solution is x = \dfrac{1}{4}.
